Works flawlessly on my Nexus 10. If you enjoyed Bridge Constructor &/or BC Playground, you will almost certainly enjoy this. It is similar to BC Playground, in that you have a lot of freedom to build and experiment with various materials and approaches. However, there are budgetary constraints and objectives for each level; some required and others optional. The game's first levels teach you the characteristics of the vehicles, and how to drive them, and then progress into building the ramps and other structures you'll use to achieve your objectives. The replay value is good, too. It's fun to go back to levels and take a different approach. Great fun!

I've played all three previous BC games.  This concept seems great, but on the very first level where you can build (not the first tutorial level, the first one where it tells you to actually build) I honestly can't figure out how to move the bridge pieces; I'm doing what the tutorial says and nothing happens.  I'm totally stuck.  Is this a bug?   I'm on a galaxy S6.  UPDATE: after force close and relaunch it's working now.  I'm not sure what was wrong previously.  UPDATE 2: I updated my wording to clarify.
replyContent: Hi Lowell! That's a tutorial level, the building and removing functions are locked at first entry to prevent newcomers from doing things they don't know yet. Only when you return to the level, building and removing is possible. To move pieces hold your finger down on a joint for a moment. When the little effect appears you can move it around.
